  <body>
   <p>The Children's Home, at 2846 Cortez Street, is owned by the Danish Church. The Reverend A. V. Andersen is the president and Mrs. Anna Petersen is the superintendent.</p>
   <p>On January 1, 1914, the Home had 23 boys and 12 girls. During the year 8 children left and 11 were admitted. During the spring of 1915 four more boys were taken in. Three girls were confirmed.</p>
   <p>Mr. Jens Nielsen, who recently died in Chicago gave his whole fortune to the Children's Home. The sum total is estimated to be about $13,000.</p>
